<xref evaluate="all" from="ROOT" n="sb;3;7242" targOrder="U" to="DITTO" type="reprint from">SB3,7242</xref></head><div lang="grc" part="N" type="edition"><ab part="N">
    <lb n="1"/><supplied cert="high" reason="lost">Ἀμ</supplied>μώνι<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">ος Ἀπίωνι τ</supplied>ῷ ἀ<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">δε</supplied>λφῷ χ<unclear cert="high" reason="undefined">αί</unclear>ρ<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">ειν</supplied>. 

    <lb n="2"/>πρὸ πάντων ἀσπά<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">ζομ</supplied><unclear cert="high" reason="undefined">αι</unclear> <unclear cert="high" reason="undefined">τ</unclear>ὴν ἀδελφὴν καὶ 

    <lb n="3"/><supplied cert="high" reason="lost">τὰ</supplied> <unclear cert="high" reason="undefined">παιδία</unclear> σου πάντα. ἐὰν δύ<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">νῃ</supplied> ἐγπλέ-

    <lb n="4"/>ξαι περσικὰ τὰ <supplied cert="high" reason="lost">ἐπ</supplied>ὶ τῆς <unclear cert="high" reason="undefined">ἀ</unclear><supplied cert="high" reason="lost">γορ</supplied>ᾶ<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">ς, μ</supplied>ὴ ἀμελήσῃς 

    <lb n="5"/>ὡς <choice><corr>εἰδὼς</corr><sic>ιδως</sic></choice> ὅτι θεῶν θελόντων ἤδη <choice><corr>μέλλει</corr><sic>μελλι</sic></choice> τὰ 

    <lb n="6"/>ὧδε καταστ<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">έ</supplied>λ<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">λε</supplied>σθαι καὶ μέλλω καὶ <choice><corr>ἐγὼ</corr><sic>καγω</sic></choice> πρὸς 

    <lb n="7"/><choice><corr>σὲ</corr><sic>σεν</sic></choice> γίνεσθαι. δι<unclear cert="high" reason="undefined">ὸ</unclear> <unclear cert="high" reason="undefined">ο</unclear>ὖν μὴ ἀμελήσῃς καὶ 

    <lb n="8"/>εἰς τ<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">ὴ</supplied>ν <choice><corr>ὠνὴν</corr><sic>ονην</sic></choice> καὶ πα<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">ρα</supplied>χρῆμα <choice><corr>σὺ</corr><sic>σ<unclear cert="high" reason="undefined">οι</unclear></sic></choice> <supplied cert="high" reason="lost">α</supplied>ὐτὰ 

    <lb n="9"/><unclear cert="high" reason="undefined">ἀ</unclear>γ<unclear cert="high" reason="undefined">ό</unclear>ρασαι. πάντ<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">ω</supplied>ς οὖ<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">ν σ</supplied>ὺ πρᾶξον ὡς <choice><corr>εἰδὼς</corr><sic>ιδως</sic></choice> 

    <lb n="10"/><supplied cert="high" reason="lost">ὅ</supplied>τι τοῦ θεοῦ <sic>θεοῦ</sic> θέλοντος τάχα καὶ <choice><corr>ἐγὼ</corr><sic>καγω</sic></choice> ἐν 

    <lb n="11"/><choice><corr>τάχει</corr><sic>ταχι</sic></choice> σε <choice><corr>κατέλαβον</corr><sic>κατελα<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">β</supplied>α</sic></choice>. εἶπον δὲ <unclear cert="high" reason="undefined">κ</unclear>α<unclear cert="high" reason="undefined">ὶ</unclear> τῷ <choice><corr>κωφῷ</corr><sic>κωπω</sic></choice> Δι-

    <lb n="12"/>ονυσίῳ <hi rend="diaeresis">ἵ</hi>να καὶ αὐτὸς ὃ ἐὰν εὕρῃ ἀγοράσῃ. 

    <lb n="13"/>καὶ δι᾽ οὗ ἐὰν εὕρῃς ἐπιστολίδιόν μοι πέμ-

    <lb n="14"/>ψον. ἀλλὰ μὴ ἀμελήσῃς μηδὲ ψυχρεύσῃ 

    <lb n="15"/>τοῦ ὅσα ἐὰν <choice><corr>ἐνῇ</corr><sic>ενην</sic></choice> ἀγοράσαι ὡς <choice><corr>εἰδὼς</corr><sic>ιδως</sic></choice> ὅτι οὐ-

    <lb n="16"/><supplied cert="high" reason="lost">δὲν</supplied> <choice><corr>μέλλεις</corr><sic>μελλις</sic></choice> <choice><corr>εἰς</corr><sic>ις</sic></choice> ἐμὲ <choice><corr>βλάπτεσθαι</corr><sic>βλαπτεσται</sic></choice> ἀλλὰ οὐ-

    <lb n="17"/>δὲ <choice><corr>λυπεῖσθαι</corr><sic>λ<unclear cert="high" reason="undefined">οι</unclear>πισται</sic></choice>. πάντως οὖν πρ<unclear cert="high" reason="undefined">ᾶγ</unclear>μά σου 

    <lb n="18"/>πρᾶξον <hi rend="diaeresis">ἵ</hi>να <unclear cert="high" reason="undefined">δι</unclear>ὰ σοῦ μόνου τὰ ὄντα <choice><corr>ᾖ</corr><sic>ην</sic></choice> 

    <lb n="19"/><unclear cert="high" reason="undefined">ἀ</unclear>γ<unclear cert="high" reason="undefined">ο</unclear>ρα<unclear cert="high" reason="undefined">σθ</unclear>έντα περσικά. πάντως μὴ ἀ-

    <lb n="20"/>μελήσῃς. ἄσ<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">π</supplied>α<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">σ</supplied><unclear cert="high" reason="undefined">αι</unclear> Παμμένην καὶ τοὺς 

    <lb n="21"/>αὐτοῦ πάντας. ἐὰν <choice><corr>χρείαν</corr><sic>χριαν</sic></choice> ἔχῃ Διονύσιος ὁ ἀδελ-

    <lb n="22"/>φός μου, ἕως δραχμῶν ἑκατὸν δὸς αὐτῷ καὶ <choice><corr>λα<supplied cert="high" reason="omitted">βὲ</supplied></corr><sic>λα</sic></choice> αὐ-

    <lb n="23"/>τὰς παρ᾽ ἐμοῦ, ἀλλὰ μὴ ἄλλως. 

    <lb n="24"/>ἐρρῶσθαί σε εὔχομαι πανοικὶ μετὰ τοῦ οἴκου 

    <lb n="25"/>σου <unclear cert="high" reason="undefined">ὅλου</unclear>, ἄδελφε Ἀπί<unclear cert="high" reason="undefined">ω</unclear><supplied cert="high" reason="lost">ν</supplied>. </ab></div><div n="meta.30783" part="N" type="description"><p><rs cert="high" type="material">Papyrus</rs></p></div><div n="meta.30783" part="N" subtype="textDate" type="commentary"><p><date notAfter="300" notBefore="201" type="textDate">III</date></p></div><div n="meta.30783" part="N" subtype="principalEdition" type="bibliography"><listBibl><bibl subtype="principal" type="publication"><title level="s" type="abbreviated">P.Ross. Georg.</title><biblScope type="volume">3</biblScope><biblScope type="numbers">3</biblScope></bibl><bibl type="Trismegistos"><biblScope type="numbers">30783</biblScope></bibl><bibl type="DDbDP"><series>0197</series>; <biblScope type="volume">3</biblScope>; <biblScope type="numbers">3</biblScope></bibl></listBibl><p>Perseus links: <xref evaluate="all" from="ROOT" href="0197;3;3" targOrder="Y" to="DITTO" type="Perseus">Text in Perseus</xref></p></div><div n="meta.30783" part="N" subtype="illustrations" type="bibliography"><p>keine</p></div><div n="meta.30783" part="N" subtype="otherPublications" type="bibliography"><head>Andere Publikationen</head><listBibl><bibl subtype="other" type="publication">SB III 7242</bibl><bibl subtype="other" type="publication">C.Pap. Hengstl 121</bibl><bibl subtype="other" type="publication">Tibiletti, Lettere private 12</bibl></listBibl></div><div n="meta.30783" part="N" subtype="translations" type="bibliography"><head>Übersetzungen</head><listBibl lang="en"><head lang="de">Englisch:</head><bibl type="translations">Johnson, Roman Egypt (1936), S. 386-387, Nr. 240.</bibl></listBibl><listBibl lang="it"><head lang="de">Italienisch:</head><bibl type="translations">Tibiletti, Lettere private (1979), 12</bibl></listBibl></div><div n="meta.30783" part="N" subtype="locations" type="history"><p><placeName cert="low" type="ancientFindspot">A